<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Abatement certificate
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. Each employer shall submit to the Area Director issuing the citation an abatement certificate with respect to each
citation item, and do so within thirty calendar days after the abatement date for the citation item.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The abatement certificate shall contain the following information:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Each citation item;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) A statement noting whether or not abatement has been accomplished with respect to each citation item and instance
listed in the citation;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) A description of the measures taken to accomplish abatement;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) The date abatement was accomplished;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) If abatement has not been accomplished, the reason(s) for not abating;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) The signature of the employer or the employer's duly authorized representative;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) The date of the signature.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the employer has initially stated in an abatement certificate that a particular citation item has not been abated,
and later the employer abates the condition, the employer shall submit to the Area Director issuing the citation a
new abatement certificate within five calendar days after abatement.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Abatement certificates for more than one citation item may be combined in a single document.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Each abatement certificate with respect to a citation item shall be accompanied by documentary evidence that
is sufficient to demonstrate clearly that the hazard has been corrected.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Abatement plan
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. (1) An Area Director may require in a citation that the employer submit a formal plan for the abatement of safety and
health violations in instances where multiple steps or long-term abatement actions are necessary.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) When called for in a citation, the employer shall prepare a written, signed, and dated abatement plan with respect
to each citation item for which the plan is required.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Abatement plans for more than one citation item may be combined within a single document.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The abatement plan shall be submitted to the Area Director issuing the citation within twenty-five calendar days
after the date of the final order or the date of the PMA final order.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Progress reports
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. An Area Director, at his or her discretion, may require progress reports in a citation where multi-step abatement
is deemed appropriate.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The Area Director shall specify the citation item with respect to which the progress reports are required, the
measures which the Area Director expects to be taken on or before the submission of each progress report, and the date
for the submission of each progress report, expressed as the number of calendar days from the date of the final order
or the date of the PMA final order.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The employer shall submit to the Area Director the requested progress reports with respect to each citation item
for which they are required under the abatement plan.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Progress reports for more than one citation item may be combined within a single document.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Progress reports shall be submitted at intervals specified by the Area Director in the citation, but the first
progress report shall not be submitted earlier than thirty calendar days after the date of the final order or the date
of the PMA final order.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Tagging cited equipment
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. (1) The employer shall affix a ``Warning'' tag on all cited equipment upon receipt of the citation.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940419-1-00031 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940419-1-00006 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) The design, application, and use of the tag required by this section shall be in accordance with 29 CFR 1910.145(f)(4).

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) In addition to the information set forth in 1910.145(f), the tag shall identify the equipment, state that a citation
has been issued, and identify where the citation is posted. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The employer shall ensure that the tag remains affixed to the cited equipment in a conspicuous location at or near
the controls of such equipment and/or the hazardous portion of the equipment, until the cited equipment is brought
into compliance with OSHA requirements or the equipment is permanently removed from service. The temporary removal
from service of cited equipment is not compliance with OSHA requirements for the purpose of this section. The protection
and posting requirements of paragraph (i)(4) of this section are also applicable to this paragraph. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Document Transmittal
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. When this section requires submission of a document to the Area Director, it may be submitted by first-class mail,
postage prepaid, facsimile transmission, or hand delivery. When the document is mailed, the date of submission is
the date of the postmark. When the document is submitted by facsimile transmission or hand delivery, the date of submission
is the date when the document is received by the Area Director.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=4 -->
Note: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
Receipt of an employer's documents by the Agency under this regulation does not constitute an agreement that the employer
is in compliance.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Accuracy of documentation
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. The employer shall assure that each statement in a document or accompanying documentation required by this section
is accurate. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Posting requirements
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. A copy of each document required to be submitted to the Area Director shall be posted, at the time of submission, at
or near each place the violation(s) described in the citation occurred. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Where, because of an employer's operations, it is not practicable to post a document at or near the location of the
violation(s), such document shall be posted, unedited, in a prominent place where it will be readily observable by
all affected employees. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Where it is physically impracticable, because of a document's size or magnitude, to post abatement plans and progress
reports, a notice to affected employees shall be posted indicating the location where the document(s) can be reviewed.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The abatement certificates, abatement plan(s) and progress reports shall be provided, upon request for examination
and copying, to employees, to employee representatives, and to the Assistant Secretary.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=4 -->
Note: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
If employers are engaged in activities which are geographically dispersed (see &sect;1903.2(b)), the document
may be posted at the location where employees report each day. If employees do not primarily work at, or report to, a
single location (see &sect;1903.2(b)), the document may be posted at the location where employees work.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(4) The employer shall assure that any document required to be posted by this section is not altered, defaced, or covered
by other material. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Any document required to be posted by this section shall remain posted until the violation has been abated, or for
six calendar days, whichever is later. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(j) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Penalties
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. Any employer failing to comply with the provisions of this section shall be subject to citation and penalty in accordance
with the provisions of Section 9 and 17 of the Act. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(k) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
False statements
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. False statements knowingly made in any document required by this section are subject to criminal penalties set forth
in section 17(g) of the Act. False statements knowingly and willfully made in any document required by this section
are subject to the criminal penalties set forth in 18 U.S.C. 1001.
