<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Recognition.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 A resident organization may request that it be recognized as the official organization representing the residents
in meetings with the HA or with other entities. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Written understanding.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 At a minimum, the HA and the RO shall put in writing their understanding concerning the elements of their relationship.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;905.965 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Funding Resident Participation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Funding will be provided under subpart J, for the following: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Resident Organizations.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Subject to appropriations, the HA shall provide funds to ROs for resident participation activities. Eligibility
to receive operating subsidy for RO activities at $25 per unit per year is a separate cost item under the Performance
Funding System. Of this amount, $15 per unit per year shall fund resident participation activities of the RO. Ten dollars
per unit per year shall fund HA costs incurred in carrying out resident participation activities. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Stipends.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 HAs may provide stipends to officers of the RO. The stipend, which may be up to $200 per month per officer, shall be decided
locally by the RO and HA. (See definition of annual income in &sect;905.102 for exclusion for these stipends.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
Tenant Opportunities Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;905.966 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Indian Tenant Opportunities Program (TOP) (which is the program similar to the public housing TOP for public housing
residents) provides technical assistance for various activities including resident management for ROs/RMCs as
authorized by Section 20 of the Act. The TOP provides opportunities for RO/RMCs to improve living conditions and resident
satisfaction in Indian housing communities. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;905.967 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Eligible TOP Activities. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Activities to be funded and carried out by an eligible resident council or resident management corporation, as defined
in subpart B, must improve the living conditions and public housing operations and may include any combination of,
but are not limited to, the following: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Resident Capacity Building.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) Training Board members in community organizing, Board development, and leadership training; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Determining the feasibility of resident management enablement for a specific project or projects; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Assisting in the actual creation of an RMC, such as consulting and legal assistance to incorporate, preparing
by-laws and drafting a corporate charter. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Resident Management.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) Training residents, as potential employees of an RMC, in skills directly related to the operation, management,
maintenance and financial systems of a project; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Training of residents with respect to fair housing requirements; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Gaining assistance in negotiating management contracts, and designing a long-range planning system. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Resident Management Business Development. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Training related to resident-owned business development and technical assistance for job training and placement
in RMC developments; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Technical assistance and training in resident managed business development through: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Feasibility and market studies; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Development of business plans; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Outreach activities; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Innovative financing methods including revolving loan funds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Legal advice in establishing resident managed business entity. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Social Support Needs (such as self-sufficiency and youth initiatives
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
). (1) Feasibility studies to determine training and social services needs; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Training in management-related trade skills, computer skills, etc; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Management-related employment training and counseling; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Coordination of support services; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Training for programs such as child care, early childhood development, parent involvement, volunteer services,
parenting skills, before and after school programs; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Training programs on health, nutrition and safety. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



