(4) Education including remedial education; literacy training; completion of secondary or post secondary education
and assistance in the attainment of certificates of high school equivalency; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Business, entrepreneurial training and counseling; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Transportation necessary to enable any participating family member to receive available services or to commute
to his/her place of employment; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Personal welfare (e.g. substance/alcohol abuse treatment and counseling, self-development counseling, etc.);

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) Supportive Health Care Services (e.g., outreach and referral services; and 
