<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) Stipends are not to be construed as salaries and should not be included as income for calculation of rents, and are
not subject to conflict of interest requirements.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Funding provided by a HA to a duly elected resident council may be made only under a written agreement between the
HA and a resident council, which includes a resident council budget and assurance that all resident council expenditures
will not contravene provisions of law and will promote serviceability, efficiency, economy and stability in the
operation of the local development. The agreement must require the local resident council to account to the HA for
the use of the funds and permit the HA to inspect and audit the resident council's financial records related to the agreement.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart C_Tenant Opportunities Program
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;964.200
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
 General.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Tenant Opportunities Program (TOP) provides technical assistance for various activities including resident
management for resident councils/resident management corporations as authorized by section 20 of the U.S. Housing
Act of 1937. The TOP provides opportunities for resident organizations to improve living conditions and resident
satisfaction in public housing communities.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) This subpart establishes the policies, procedures and requirements for participating in the TOP with respect
to applications for funding for programs identified in this subpart.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) This subpart contains the policies, procedures and requirements for the resident management program as authorized
by section 20 of the U.S. Housing Act of 1937.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;964.205
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
 Eligibility.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Resident councils/resident management corporations.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Any eligible resident council/resident management corporation as defined in subpart B is eligible to participate
in a program administered under this subpart.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Activities.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Activities to be funded and carried out by an eligible resident council or resident management corporation, as defined
in subpart B, must improve the living conditions and public housing operations and may include any combination of,
but are not limited to, the following: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Resident Capacity Building.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (i) Training Board members in community organizing, Board development, and leadership training;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Determining the feasibility of resident management enablement for a specific project or projects; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Assisting in the actual creation of an RMC, such as consulting and legal assistance to incorporate, preparing
by-laws and drafting a corporate charter.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Resident Management.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (i) Training residents, as potential employees of an RMC, in skills directly related to the operation, management,
maintenance and financial systems of a project;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Training of residents with respect to fair housing requirements; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Gaining assistance in negotiating management contracts, and designing a long-range planning system.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Resident Management Business Development.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (i) Training related to resident-owned business development and technical assistance for job training and placement
in RMC developments;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Technical assistance and training in resident managed business development through:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) Feasibility and market studies;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Development of business plans;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Outreach activities; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) Innovative financing methods including revolving loan funds; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Legal advice in establishing resident managed business entity.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Social Support Needs (such as self-sufficiency and youth initiatives).
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (i) Feasibility studies to determine training and social services needs;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Training in management-related trade skills, computer skills, etc.;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Management-related employment training and counseling;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Coordination of support services;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



